br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 12:09:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Greetings Magicians of the Board.  I was curious as to what each of your opinions is about who is the best partner for a magician.  The magician and partner should be able to be self sufficient. I was thinking cleric/magician but was curious as to what all of you think.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your replies <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 2:34:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> I'd say Necro, but Shamans and Druids also make excellent partners. <p><html>
<img src="http://www.magecompendium.com/Images/Reaper.gif" height="135" width="90" >
<centre><b>Renesh, Level 41 Magician <br>
Reneshen Daemonsbane, Level 32 Paladin <br>
Reneshenn, Level 20 Rogue <br>

</b>
</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=babalum>Babalum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 8:14:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Anythint that adds : </span><hr size=1> Anything that adds :<br>
<br>
Escapability (crowd control &amp; Run-as-hell-thingies!)<br>
Damage<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unabienincinerador.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nabien Incinerador</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/fire10.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 9:38:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Anythint that adds : </span><hr size=1> depends on where you are, but good partners will make up for your weaknesses.  Druids, wizzards, shamans, clerics, necros all pair up with us well. <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/Sig1test.jpg> <BR>
Ambassador of <a href="http://www.thestonecutters.org"> The Stone Cutters</a> <BR>
<a href="http://frontpage.webzone.net/shep/povarcentral.htm">Povar Central</a> <BR>
<I> Mages, EQ's walking K-Mart. </I> <BR>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ommundan>Ommundan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.datecc.de/bilder/woag/bilder/misc/misc59d.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/29/02 4:09:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> mageboy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 12:25:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   personally.....</span><hr size=1> I like enchanters...<br>
<br>
1. clarity all the time<br>
2. crowd control<br>
3. pet buffs<br>
<br>
The only thing a mage/ench combo lacks is ease of travel but...who cares when everyone camps anyway? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Lunasicc</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 2:10:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Enchanters</span><hr size=1> I would say enchanters because they have strengths in all our weak area's.<br>
<br>
We have NO crowd control.<br>
We have NO mana recovery spells.<br>
<br>
Those 2 things are enchanter's bread and butter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubikkinrn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BikkinRN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 5:31:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters</span><hr size=1> Enchanter and a Wizard, 2 pets, 3 good dd's, dots from chanter, clairty, crowd control, Enchanter has fear, wiz has snare. <p>Bikkin PinkCurtains

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 6:08:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'd say the top three, in order, are:<br>
<br>
1. Necromancers.   Given the right situation there is no more powerful duo in the game.   Fear-Kite with two pets holding Sword of Runes thowing down the smack down.  At higher levels you can not only hold very tough spots but do almost constant pulls from them.  (When I hit lvl 51 a lvl 52 Necro friend of mine and me pulled from Skyfire almost constantly and threw the beatdown on mature wurms, wyverns, etc.).  Seriously, this duo is awesome given the right situation -- the right situation being a place to fear-kite.  Necro's add healing, crowdcontrol, pet, fear-kite, etc.<br>
<br>
2. Druids.  Druids compliment Magicians almost perfectly.  Magicians are the best Kiters in the game so long as we have SoW :)  Druids allow quick travel, heals, DD's, SoW/Snare, and Harmony -- Harmony is a huge plus when breaking outdoor spawns.  <br>
<br>
3. Enchanters.  Obviously, clarity is nice, and Enchanters help break spawns and control bad situations.  Definately the best pairing if you want to go into a dungeon.  I'd choose either Necros or Druids for outdoor zones, but Enchanters win hands down on the inside.  <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usimmulcrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Simm Ulcrum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 6:22:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Best Partner</span><hr size=1> I usually party with a cleric and enchanter with a Shadow Knight thrown in for variety.  Its pretty sweet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uleguingaramonde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leguin Garamonde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/00 7:23:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner</span><hr size=1> I'd say after 39 a Cleric would be your best bet if you're going after single big mobs. Between your ability to recast pets (between 200 and 400 mana depending on how high you are) and their ability to cheal your pet, that adds up to ALOT of damage being delt out before either of your are going low on mana. Alternate CHealing and pet Recasting to keep an elemental on the mob at all times, and damage shield your pet so the enemy is continually taking hits. This will add up to be a good wad of damage, and you can meditate back most of the mana between your pet dying twice (one time it dies, you resummon, next time it's near death, it's CHealed, then next time you resummon). <br>
<br>
Necros, Shamen, Enchanters, Druids, and Wizards (any casters I'm leaving out) also make good partners too. Mages can group with most of the casting classes out there extremely effectively! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthemissilverlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Themis Silverlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/16/00 6:52:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> I think we clerics make pretty darn good partners for mages.Pet always near full health, constant pulls, easy to do againstone to two mobs. hp/ac, ac, and symbol buffs make that awesomepet into a REALLY awesome pet. <p><P><P ALIGN=LEFT>
<FORM><SELECT>
<OPTION>Pick Your Poison
<OPTION>[44 Cleric] Themis Silverlight (Human)
<OPTION>[27 Druid] Rhylan Overkyll (Human)
<OPTION>[15 Magician] Minithemis (Gnome)
<OPTION>[14 Bard] Bhrody (Human)
</SELECT></FORM></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urredre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rredre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/00 5:31:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Rogue. Keep fire shields on the Rogue and pet and let the pettaunt it each time the rogue backstabs the two of them will justshred mobs.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waldenawildfyre>Waldena Wildfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/00 12:06:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Mage and rogue is bad combo..pets dont accually taunt that well and after rogues backstab hits he/she is gonna take some damage.  And if you wait for them to recover b4 you fight again you will get slow xp then you would solo..and if you continue your rate of pulls as if you were solo rogue will either die or be sitting and resting while you get do they kill..rogue sucks in free xp.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umodauth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>modauth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(7/15/02 12:47:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Id say necro by far. With a necro you can do mobs that under  normal circumstances are very difficult solo for the mere factor that the mob is going to tear your pets apart so you end up chaining. And as others have said a darkness/fear ensures your pet and theirs is never getting too much dmg. Get to 54 and take a 53+ necro. Two rogue pets in a fear kiting situation? /me drools its just .... amazing. <p><div align=center>
Ianieng Vith`rell<br>
55 Conjurer<br>
Knights of Takhisis<br>
Veeshan<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=120794"> My lowbie stuff :(  </a>
</div><br>
<div align=center>
14 pieces and counting!</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchoythemonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Choy the monk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(7/16/02 12:54:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Magicians are the best Kiters in the game so long as we have SoW <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
<br>
How many mages do you see quad kiting =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvillsolro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vill SolRo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(7/16/02 7:53:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> I agree.. rogues not good for partners.<br>
<br>
Anyone that plays a mage should know there is some type of coding verant put in, which gives players more taunt than pets.  As soon as a melee enters melee range of pet/mob fight, the mob will turn on the PC instantly.. pets can't taunt off of a pc.<br>
<br>
That has been my observation anyway. <p>Vill ShadowVenom 45 Rogue
