<br>
    For indoor zones, I prefer a full group, rather than a partner. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubandose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bandose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#333333>(7/17/02 12:35:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> ANY class is great with a mage.  Unfortunately, rogues offer the least amount of benefit, however, some benefit still remains.<br>
<br>
I think many mages forget or haven't learned to use their &quot;penalties&quot; as bonuses.  Grouping with a warrior?  Here's two great tactics:<br>
<br>
1) Tank pulls, when mob is in fighting area, sick the pet on it (DS'd of course).  When the pet's HPs get to approx 20 percent, the tank enters battle to finish the mob off.  The pets DO NOT HOLD ATTENTION on any mob, therefore any tank can instantly take the aggro by entering melee range.  Since pets heal 10x faster than PCs, it's stupid on the team's part to not take advantage of this.  The warrior takes far less damage and you're up and in action that much quicker.  Without a healer, this can be done to do about 50 percent more battles before rest.  With a healer who puts a nice regen (like Nature's Touch) on the pet, this can almost go non-stop.<br>
<br>
2) If you've got some UBER tank who's AC is just insane (say 1500), then let them tank.  You make a water pet and let the tank know you pet will backstab.  It's easy to get mobs into a backstabbing position for a pet cause they're NEVER look at the pet as long as the tank stays in melee range.  Say what you will, but the 60 water pet does FAR more damage than the epic pet using this tactic.<br>
<br>
Now, most import for you new mages.  For Tunare's sack, LEARN YOUR MOBS!  Gonna go fight a caster mob, use air or epic pet.  Going after a mob that runs away and does so quickly - if in a dungeon, use earth pet for roots.  In the open, use water for backstab (if you speed the water pet up) or air for stuns (can't run when stunned).<br>
<br>
Fire pets, well, past 49, it belongs on the last page with your lvl 4 pets.  Nice to have the spell, that's about it.  Maybe verant will wake up on these some day. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujoleena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Joleena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/02 5:10:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Until PoP vastly improves current methods of getting around the world I would say either a Wizard or a Druid.  Its nice when you spend next to no time traveling and almost all your time hunting.  It sucks when you go to hunt someplace find it over-camped and have to spend time traveling to another spot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usenjivaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SenjiVaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 4:35:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> Best partner ... Cleric hands down <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32137"><b>Senji</b></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucanvashan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>canvashan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 7:48:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best Partner for a Magician</span><hr size=1> I'm surprised that very few mentioned Shamans.  Shamans are better than Clerics IMHO.  Shamans have BEST slow in the game.  When shaman slows a mob, it means pets taks less damage.  Less damage means lesser heals and they don't have to drain their mana healing pets like clerics do.  Shamans can also land dots, Malo, and use their pets (even though they are alot weaker) too.  I usually let my pet tank first to build aggro and shammy sends his/her pet later to help out on dmg output.<br>
During the down time,  their HP regen (Torpor is ver nice) spell works great with mod rod 2.  I'll be full mana just in few minutes and shammies also chew up their hp to get their own mana and don't require my mod rod.  We usually have little down time and that gives us more XP.<br>
Shamans can do little crowd control also.  They can root and dot mobs while fighting other mob.  <br>
<br>
I say Shamans are one of the TOP choices.<br>
